      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "tone": "info",
          "title": "Also",
          "body": "The Dish; 1 quantity katsu curry sauce; 40g mixed salad leaves."
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Place the oil in a saucepan over a medium heat, and add the chopped onion, garlic and ginger and cook until softened."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Lower the heat, add the spices and cook for 2¿3 minutes while stirring"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the flour and stir over the heat, then slowly add stock"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Bring to a simmer and add the coconut milk, soy sauce and sugar, to taste."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sieve the mixture for a smooth sauce"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cut each chicken breast in half and open it out like a book, then put under cling film and flatten out with a rolling pin until it's about 1cm thick. Then place flour, eggs and breadcrumbs in three separate bowls and dip each chicken breast first in flour, then egg and then breadcrumbs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Place the oil on a medium-high heat. Fry one coated breast at a time for 3¿4 minutes on each side then transfer to a plate lined with baking paper"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Spoon a portion of rice, cooked to packet instructions, onto two serving plates."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Slice the deep-fried chicken breasts into strips at an angle and arrange on top of the rice."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ladle the curry sauce over the chicken and rice and place the salad on the side with a drizzle of dressing"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Curry tastes raw or harsh",
              "cause": "Spices weren't bloomed in oil long enough before the wet ingredients went in.",
              "fix": "Fry whole spices first, then ground spices for a minute in hot oil before adding onions or liquid. The aroma changes when it's ready."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Sauce is split or oily",
              "cause": "Cooked too hard after adding dairy, or yoghurt added straight from the fridge.",
              "fix": "Bring yoghurt to room temperature first and stir it in off the heat. Don't boil curries with yoghurt or cream — simmer only."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Meat is tough",
              "cause": "Cut too lean, or cooked at a rolling boil.",
              "fix": "Use cuts with connective tissue (thigh, shoulder, shin). Keep the curry at a gentle simmer for the long-cook cuts — bubbles barely breaking the surface."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Heat is uneven — fiery in places, mild elsewhere",
              "cause": "Chilli added late and not stirred through.",
              "fix": "Add chillies early with the aromatics so the heat distributes. Taste before serving and adjust with chilli flakes if needed."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Vegetarian: swap meat for paneer cubes or chickpeas. Add at the simmer stage so they take on the sauce."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Coconut version: replace half the stock with coconut milk for a milder, richer curry."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make a day ahead; the flavour deepens overnight in the fridge."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Chinese home cooking favours bright contrast: salt, sweet, sour, heat, working against each other in one bowl. The dish lands somewhere on that grid — adjust the balance to suit your palate."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
